@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Lightnix' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Lightnix runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  The game starts with 10 tiles of various shapes, randomly placed
on the board. To play, just click on one of these tiles. This will
generate 'lightning bolts' that will start from the clicked tile
and each lightning bolt will continue to move until it gets to the
border or another tile. If that tile is identical to the one from
which the lightning bolt started from, it will be eliminated. Note
that the clicked tile will remain intact.

  You get points according to the number of tiles that have been
eliminated by the 4 lightning bolts, as shown on the following
table:

  1 tile  = 1 point
  2 tiles = 10 points
  3 tiles = 100 points
  4 tiles = 1000 points

  The game counts the consecutive number of times that lightning
bolts did not eliminate any tile, and add that number of tiles on
the board each time. Once a tile is eliminated, that number is
resetted to zero. Do not let the game board fill up completely, if
that happens, the game will end.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

